[XLA:GPU] Add ScaledDotRewriter to the GPU compiler.

This pass rewrites `scaled-dot` HLO instructions into a sequence of `convert`, `broadcast`, `multiply`, and `dot` operations. The `scaled-dot` operands and scales are first converted to BF16. The scales are then broadcast and reshaped to match the operand shapes. Finally, element-wise multiplications are performed between operands and their respective scales, and the results are used as inputs to a standard `dot` instruction.

We run it unconditionally because we don't have any support for the scaled-dot on the codegen side.

To diagnose a persistent cross-platform rendering issue, this commit introduces a new helper function, `parseXmlString`. This function wraps the browser's `DOMParser` and checks for a `<parsererror>` element in the output.

If a parsing error is found, the error details and the problematic XML string are logged to the console. All existing `DOMParser` calls have been replaced with this new function.

This change is intended to gather data on how different browsers/OSes parse the XML files within a presentation, to identify the root cause of the rendering inconsistencies.

issue.title: Fix: clear duplicate-casing errors after case-only file renames on Windows (closes #261995)
issue.body: On case-insensitive file systems (Windows for example) renaming a file by only changing its letter-case ~ for example `page1.js` => `Page1.js` ~ confuses `tsserver`. It continues to hold both casings in the program and surfaces errors such as: The error persists until the user manually restarts the TS server or reloads VS Code (see bug #261995). ### RCA File-watcher stacks don’t always emit a delete => create sequence for a case-only rename on case-insensitive FSs. `tsserver` therefore never drops the old path and thinks the file is duplicated. ### Testing * Verified on Windows 11. ### Files changed * `extensions/typescript-language-features/src/languageFeatures/updatePathsOnRename.ts` * `extensions/typescript-language-features/src/typeScriptServiceClientHost.ts` --- Closes #261995

issue.title: Searching artists by # of items in their gallery
issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe**

Pretty tough to find artists that specialize in a certain niche. E.g. I want a list of artists that usually draw cat girls (a random number would be maybe, artists with at least 50 pieces of art tagged as 'cat girl'). I can click around in the cat girl tag, but that's likely to lead me to a bunch of artists that have only drawn a cat girl once. 

**Describe the solution you'd like**

A way to filter artists based on how much of X they have in their gallery. E.g. there's a box you can type a number in + specify a tag, and artists that don't meet that threshold don't appear. 

**Describe alternatives you've considered**

Manually finding artists. 

**Additional context**

N/A, thanks if you choose this.

comment.body:
Hello 👋 

Grabber, while it has some local features, mostly just forwards requests to the website to find results. So unless a given website has a way to return tags that have X number of images with another tag in their search results, that seem like a pretty complex thing to do.
The alternative on Grabber's side would be to load _all_ results, and only then filter them based on the tag criteria, but that seem quite the intensive thing to do 😅

On the other hand, some websites do provide some cross-tag search feature, like Danbooru. Maybe that would help you?
https://danbooru.donmai.us/related_tag?search[query]=cat_girl&search[category]=Artist

1) if no filters exist (such as in a first use of Gramps) then the filter list having zero items caused an error.
2) there are 2 different <kbd>Import</kbd> buttons doing different things. 1st in the FilterParams dialog, 2nd in the clipboard text editor dialog. These buttons should have different labeling to make instructions less ambiguous.  
3) The semi-modal dialogs (confirmation and errors) spawned from the Clipboard editor window are not "top level" dialogs. They can become hidden beneath the Clipboard editor window. They should be modal and top-level.  
4) the modality and parentage of the Clipboard editor is muddled. If you click on the FilterParams dialog while the Clipboard editor is active, the editor disappears but still blocks other operations. (pressing the <kbd>Esc</kbd> key will dismiss the hidden dialog.) Clicking another part of the Gramps gui pushes the editor dialog behind the FilterParams layer but at least the dialog does not disappear.

posted install and Import/Export instructions to Discourse
https://gramps.discourse.group/t/sharing-custom-filters/997/5

comment.body: Thanks, I will take a look at these issues.
